  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establishing the foundations and strengthening capacities in the Peruvian government for reducing wildlife trafficking in border areas with other countries in the tropical Andes trade and trafficking in the tropical Andes</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Conserve biodiversity and manage natural resources in ways that maintain their long-term viability and preserve their potential to meet the needs of present and future generations. Activities include combating illegal and corrupt exploitation of natural resources and the control of invasive species. Programs in this element should be integrated with the Agriculture Area under Economic Growth and Conflict Mitigation and Reconciliation Area under the Peace and Security Category, when applicable and appropriate.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award strives to conserve biodiversity and manage natural resources in ways that maintain their long-term viability and preserve their potential to meet the needs of present and future generations. Activities include combating illegal and corrupt exploitation of natural resources and the control of invasive species. This includes other threatened and iconic forest and aquatic. The purpose of this project is to (i) gather and analyze data on wildlife trafficking in Peru, and design and pilot-test an integrated database that can later be shared with and used by Ecuador and other countries across the Tropical Andes; (ii) strengthen the capacities of Peruvian governmental agencies to implement multi-agency cooperative law enforcement protocols and procedures for controlling wildlife trafficking in border areas; and (iii) disseminate the results and lessons learned both in Peru and transnationally with other countries across the Tropical Andes to raise awareness about best practices and available resources and tools to effectively combat wildlife trafficking in the region..</narrative>
  </description>
